PN,39602
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1772132672
OL,3,CFormer football club owner loses bid
OL,4,Cto appeal against fraud convictions
OL,6,FHe was convicted in May 2023 of two
OL,7,Fcounts of fraudulent trading, fraud by
OL,8,Ffalse representation and being
OL,9,Finvolved in the acquisition,
OL,10,Fretention, use or control of the
OL,11,Fproceeds of fraudulently mis-sold
OL,12,Fenergy contracts, following a trial at
OL,13,FPreston Crown Court.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39603
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1772132672
OL,3,CFormer football club owner loses bid
OL,4,Cto appeal against fraud convictions
OL,6,FAt the Court of Appeal on 24 February,
OL,7,Fbarristers for Pilley said his
OL,8,Fconvictions were unsafe as he
OL,9,Fexperienced "disadvantage through
OL,10,Fdifference" as a result of his
OL,11,Fattention deficit hyperactivity
OL,12,Fdisorder (ADHD) not being recognised
OL,13,Fat the time of his trial.
OL,15,FThe Crown Prosecution Service opposed
OL,16,Fthe appeal bid at the two-day hearing
OL,17,Fin London.
OL,26,@qD@MOUrD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39604
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1772132672
OL,3,CFormer football club owner loses bid
OL,4,Cto appeal against fraud convictions
OL,6,FIn a ruling on 25 February, Lord
OL,7,FJustice Edis, sitting with Mrs Justice
OL,8,FO'Farrell and Judge Andrew Menary KC,
OL,9,Fdismissed the challenge, stating:
OL,10,F"There is no arguable basis upon which
OL,11,Fthis appeal could depend."
OL,13,FNational Trading Standards said in May
OL,14,F2023 that the fraud related to a "web
OL,15,Fof interconnected companies that
OL,16,Fmisled innocent small businesses"
OL,17,Fnationwide.
OL,26,@rD@AOUsD@ZO]vD@bOUxD@aO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39605
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1772132672
OL,3,CFormer football club owner loses bid
OL,4,Cto appeal against fraud convictions
OL,6,FThey continued that Pilley and others
OL,7,F"were responsible for targeting small
OL,8,Fbusiness owners and deceiving them
OL,9,Finto signing long-term energy
OL,10,Fcontracts between 2014 and 2016".
OL,12,FPilley stepped down as chairman of
OL,13,FFleetwood Town following the trial,
OL,14,Fwith the club stating at the time that
OL,15,Fthe convictions "are against
OL,16,Findividuals and not Fleetwood Town FC,
OL,17,For any of the businesses associated
OL,18,Fwith them".
OL,26,@oD@AOUrD@`O]wD@QOUzD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39606
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1772132672
OL,3,CFormer football club owner loses bid
OL,4,Cto appeal against fraud convictions
OL,6,FAdrian Darbishire KC, representing
OL,7,FPilley at the Court of Appeal, said on
OL,8,FTuesday that the impact of his
OL,9,Fclient's "unrecognised disability" on
OL,10,Fthe trial "renders the convictions
OL,11,Funsafe".
OL,13,FHe continued that Pilley did "very
OL,14,Fbadly in the witness box" in ways
OL,15,Fwhich were "completely consistent"
OL,16,Fwith someone showing the symptoms of
OL,17,FADHD, which in turn would have
OL,18,Faffected the jury's impression of him.
OL,26,@qD@JOUqD@bO]rD@KOUsD@GO]uD@^OUvD@YO]wD@
OL,26,ALOUwD@bO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39607
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1772132672
OL,3,CFormer football club owner loses bid
OL,4,Cto appeal against fraud convictions
OL,6,FHe said: "It would be the height of
OL,7,Fnaivety, or even disingenuous, to
OL,8,Fpretend that the jury will decide a
OL,9,Fcase irrespective of the way in which
OL,10,Fa defendant gives evidence."
OL,12,FLord Justice Edis said in his ruling
OL,13,Fthat the prosecution's case was "based
OL,14,Fupon extensive documentary evidence"
OL,15,Fand that Pilley was "able to engage
OL,16,Fwith complex material" during the
OL,17,Ftrial.
OL,26,@nD@JOUrD@\O]uD@aOUvD@dO]wD@UOUxD@VO]
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/8
OL,2,W/*%+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,397,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39608
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F396A1772132672
OL,3,CFormer football club owner loses bid
OL,4,Cto appeal against fraud convictions
OL,6,FHe said: "The jury's conclusions
OL,7,Fdepended upon that material and
OL,8,F(Pilley's) explanation, rather than
OL,9,Fsolely upon their impression of his
OL,10,Fdemeanour."
OL,12,FHe continued that Pilley was a "highly
OL,13,Fcapable and successful businessman",
OL,14,Fand that his career achievements
OL,15,Fprovided "significant real-world
OL,16,Fevidence of his capacity to cope with
OL,17,Fcomplex information".
OL,26,@nD@JOUpD@ApmpD@JpnrD@KO]tD@`OUuD@cO]wD@
OL,26,AJOUyD@TO]
